Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 400 degrees. Shuck and cut the @Corn on the Cob{1} kernels off the cob. Thinly slice the @Persian Cucumber{2}. Halve the @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @Chives{1/4%ounce}. Cut the @Lemon{1} into wedges.

Toss the cucumbers, tomatoes, @White Wine Vinegar{2%tablespoon}, 1 Tablespoon chives, and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} together in a #medium bowl{}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Paprika{1%teaspoon}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Place the @Chicken Thighs{12%ounce} in a medium bowl with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Turn to thoroughly coat. Press each chicken thigh into the panko mixture. Set aside.

Cook the chicken: Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the chicken. Cook ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until golden brown but not yet cooked through. Reduce the heat if the chicken is browning too quickly. Transfer the pan to the oven to finish cooking, about ~{8%minutes}.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, transfer the chicken to a baking sheet after browning each side.

Cook the corn: Meanwhile, brown @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Once melted, add the corn. Cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until the corn is golden and the butter is browned and fragrant. Season with salt and pepper.

Plate and serve: Serve the crispy chicken alongside the cucumber tomato salad and brown-butter corn. Squeeze the lemon wedges over the chicken and garnish with the remaining chives. Enjoy!